######################### Line by Line Explanation
import seaborn as sns
Imports the Seaborn library.
sns is a short name used for Seaborn.

Seaborn is used for data visualization and plotting graphs.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
Imports Matplotlib pyplot module.

plt is a short name.

Used for displaying graphs and adding titles, labels, etc.

LOAD DATASET
df = sns.load_dataset("titanic")
Loads the inbuilt Titanic dataset from Seaborn.

Dataset is stored in variable df.

df means DataFrame.

print("========== DATA PREVIEW ==========")
Prints heading for output section.

print(df.head())
Displays first 5 rows of dataset.

Helps to preview data.

print("\n========== DATA INFO ==========")
Prints heading for dataset information.

print(df.info())
Shows information about dataset:
Number of rows and columns
Data types
Missing values

BOXPLOT
print("\n========== BOXPLOT ==========")
Prints heading for boxplot section.
sns.boxplot(x="sex", y="age", hue="survived", data=df)
Creates a box plot.

Parameters:
x="sex"
Gender on X-axis.
Male and Female categories.

y="age"
Age values on Y-axis.
hue="survived"
Separates data based on survival.
0 = Not Survived
1 = Survived
data=df

Uses Titanic dataset.

TITLE AND LABELS
plt.title("Age Distribution by Gender and Survival")
Adds title to graph.

plt.xlabel("Gender")
Labels X-axis as Gender.

plt.ylabel("Age")
Labels Y-axis as Age.

plt.show()
Displays the boxplot graph.

OBSERVATIONS
print("\n========== OBSERVATIONS ==========")
Prints heading for observations.

print("1. Females have higher survival rate than males.")
Observation from graph:

More females survived compared to males.

print("2. Children (lower age) have higher survival chances.")
Younger passengers survived more.

print("3. Male age distribution is wider than females.")
Male ages are more spread out.

print("4. Older passengers have lower survival rate.")
Older people survived less.

print("5. Some outliers are present in age.")
Some age values are far from normal range.
These are called outliers.

###########Important Viva/Oral Questions

What is Box Plot?
A box plot is a graphical representation used to show:

Median
Quartiles
Outliers
Spread of data

What is Seaborn?
Seaborn is a Python visualization library built on Matplotlib used for attractive statistical graphs.

What is Matplotlib?
Matplotlib is a Python library used for plotting charts and graphs.

What is hue in Seaborn?
hue is used to divide data into categories using different colors.

What is Outlier?
An outlier is a value that is very different from other values in dataset.

What does head() do?
head() displays first 5 rows of dataset.

What does info() do?
info() gives summary information about dataset including data types and missing values.


